description.narrative: As at October 2019, 190,298 children aged 6–23 months had received MNP supplementation. This translates to 81% coverage against an annual coverage target of 73%, indicating significant achievement. About 130,050 pregnant women received IFA supplementation (60% against an annual target of 91%), with the slow progress due to stockouts of supplies. The first round of the Vitamin A supplementation campaign reached 622,799 children aged 6–59 months. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
